1	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2	// parseJsonlToTurns ŌĆö convert claude-agent-sdk's native jsonl transcript
3	// (`~/.claude/projects/<slug>/<sessionId>.jsonl`) into the canonical
4	// `Turn[]` shape that channel-web's history-adapter already consumes.
5	//
6	// Two design rules:
7	//
8	//   1. Every produced ContentBlock MUST round-trip through
9	//      `ContentBlockSchema.safeParse`. The jsonl on disk is untrusted at
10	//      our boundary (per Invariant I5 ŌĆö untrusted-content stays untrusted
11	//      at every hop): the SDK is third-party code and the model output it
12	//      transcribes is by definition adversarial. Drop blocks that fail
13	//      validation; the surviving blocks still ship.
14	//
15	//   2. The function is total: malformed input never throws. Truncated
16	//      tails (mid-flush writes from a live SDK process), corrupt mid-file
17	//      lines, unknown `type` values, and empty files all yield well-typed
18	//      output ŌĆö `[]` in the worst case.
19	//
20	// Two behaviors that diverge from "1 jsonl line == 1 Turn":
21	//
22	//   - tool_result remap. A user-type line whose content carries any
23	//     tool_result block becomes role='tool' (not 'user'). The channel-web
24	//     history-adapter routes role='tool' into the assistant lane; without
25	//     this remap a tool result would render as if the user typed it. This
26	//     also matches what the legacy runner emitted via `chat:turn-end` ŌĆö
27	//     `role:'tool'` for tool_result-bearing emissions.
28	//
29	//   - Same-message.id coalesce. The SDK splits a logical assistant
30	//     message that mixes text + tool_use across two consecutive jsonl
31	//     lines (different uuid, same `message.id`). We append the second
32	//     line's blocks onto the first emitted Turn so the consumer sees one
33	//     assistant Turn with both blocks in order. Cross-message coalescing
34	//     (i.e. text ŌåÆ tool_use ŌåÆ tool_result ŌåÆ followup-text) is NOT done
35	//     here; granularity within a multi-step interaction will still
36	//     differ from what the legacy runner emitted.
37	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
38	
